The program below should create a file with the single
byte 255, but instead the file created is of length 0.

gcc 2.0, library: lib92.03.25
----------test.c------------
#include <stdio.h>

main()
{	FILE *fd;
	char buf[80];

	fd = fopen("dummy", "w");
	buf[0] = 255;
	fwrite(buf, 1, 1, fd);
	fclose(fd);
}

